<br>
God loot is the best method, as long as you can trust your loot distributors to do their job fairly.  It gears the guild faster, with less items rotting and items going to classes that can make the best use of them.  In my guild, we track all of the loots, so that if anyone thinks that loot is being awarded unfairly, they can talk to us and we can look it up, and make changes if needed.  <br>
<br>
The /random method is not used by any high end guild, but it is probably a good method for the more casual raiding guild that has a lot of casual players. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bonlainyt>BonlainyT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mangina Deluxe</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/13/03 2:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4142.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DKP is not the best</span><hr size=1> If that was biting humor then I doubt it and I will ever get along.  My loss I guess. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247362"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:aqua;font-family:Dauphin ;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bonlainy Trueheart WALKERS<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Epic Crusader, Vazaelle</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thenerple>TheNerple</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/13/03 3:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4142.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DKP is not the best</span><hr size=1> [quoteThere are a couple other problems with DKP. I've heard of people coming back after a 3 month break just to spend their points in order to increase the value of their character on ebay. Also, droppable items will often be bid on just so that the person can sell them for cash. Finally, many loots will sometimes go to a class that won't really benefit as much as other classes (hybrids bidding on flowing thought items when your clerics/wizards etc. can make better use of them)[/quote]<br>
<br>
You'll find most guilds with an established points system police themselves rather nicely. It's quickly learned that not bidding on items that are clearly better for others helps you get the items that will be amazing for your class.  For example Rangers and Rogues have alot of equipment in common.  If a Piercer drops with a backstab modifier on it, you wotn see a Ranger bid on it soa  Rogue gets it, and in turn the Rogues wont bid on a great DPS bow that drops just for stats so the Ranger can pick it up.  That way there is alot less competition for items you really want and you are just competing against others of your class or similiar classes.  There are always going to be some shady dealing going on, but that is the same with all systems.  Most conflicts end up being when 2 classes can use for 2 different reasons.  For example a bow with a lot of HP on it dropping. What's a better use for it, DPS for Rangers or HP on tanks?  Either way the item is going to get alot used effieciently so it doesnt matter.<br>
<br>
About people coming back after breaks, there are easy way to stop this, usually by inserting clauses that either freeze points until a player is back long enough to contribute or resetting points to a low value. <br>
<br>
You'll find most points systems are modified to suit the guild's needs. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=180392&amp;resize=true">Nerple Reveler</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
