If you ask me, the BEST method is a god/dkp hybrid.  Person in charge decides what classes can best use an item and allows only them to bid.  He/she also decides special circumstances (a tank w/ 100hp belt wants a 125hp belt, and he isn't allowed b/c 2 tanks there only have 50hp belts).  This system would eliminate all the downfalls of both systems, and keeps the strengths of each. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rynznreap>Rynz NReap</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/13/03 3:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4142.topic&index=23>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/philomath/Squirl.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DKP is not the best</span><hr size=1> &quot;I've heard of people coming back after a 3 month break just to spend their points in order to increase the value of their character on ebay&quot;<br>
<br>
/nod this does suck however if they raided for all the time to gather up enough points, without looting anything then one would assume the deserve an item.  However if it is known that a person is going to e-bay then I don't think any guilds with DKP would let a person loot.  Even the God loot system fails here, if someone has been to many many raids with no loot they should have a better chance of getting a loot drop (which would be e-bayed as well).  The problem here is decietful people not the system.<br>
<br>
&quot;droppable items will often be bid on just so that the person can sell them for cash.&quot;<br>
<br>
Most DKP systems I have seen, items can only be bid on by people who can use them for a main.  If they go off and sell said item how is that different than being God awarded an item and selling it?<br>
<br>
&quot;many loots will sometimes go to a class that won't really benefit as much as other classes (hybrids bidding on flowing thought items when your clerics/wizards etc. can make better use of them&quot;<br>
<br>
This is true.  A Wizzard or Cleric who only attends raids rarely may not get a highly prizzed item while the hybrids who is alwyas there gets a  FT items.  However any Casters who attend raids regularly will have the points to get such items.  If you have a Hybrid with so many points as to get his 'needed' items (DPS weapons, nice HP items) as well as bid of FT items, then he must really show up and help the guild whenever he can.  This is a great asset to the guild and perhaps he should get a FT item.<br>
<br>
&quot;as long as you can trust your loot distributors&quot;<br>
<br>
It has nothing to do with trust.  It has everything to do with perception.  Every time an officer gets loot it can be percieved as favoritism, whether it is or not.  It breeds contempt and anomosity.  Even if the Officers keep good track of who got what the members usually do not.  I also have yet to see god loot systems where it is published who got what so there is no way to check to see if distribution was fair.  It is all about perception.<br>
<br>
&quot;In my guild, we track all of the loots, so that if anyone thinks that loot is being awarded unfairly&quot;<br>
<br>
Is it published in a place where all members can see or do they have to ask an officer?  If they have to ask then again it goes to perception.  If it is published openly then you have overcome one of the worst parts of God loot system and Kudos to you.  By published I mean not just who got what that day but who got what over time etc...<br>
<br>
&quot;/random method is not used by any high end guild&quot;<br>
<br>
The rand method sucks God loot is better than it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=353574">Razt</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
